SSL Cerfificate                 https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11804202/how-do-i-setup-a-ssl-certificate-for-an-express-js-server

add this to the app.js file:


const fs = require('fs');
var privateKey = fs.readFileSync( 'privatekey.pem' );
var certificate = fs.readFileSync( 'certificate.pem' );


https.createServer({
    key: privateKey,
    cert: certificate
}, app).listen(443);          at the end of the app



download the ssl key file from domain provider
downloas the ssl certificate

bouth naming into a  .pem file!


add the key file to the node app folder (root works)



